# DS0 — Cursor Rules
# This file points to the shared rules. Do NOT edit rules here.

Read and follow ALL instructions in `.ai/RULES.md` before every task.
Read any additional context files in the `.ai/` directory as needed.

## Cursor-Specific Instructions

- When referencing files, use @-mentions (e.g., @.ai/RULES.md)
- Use multi-file edit when generating a full component (all files at once)
- After generating code, run terminal commands to validate:
  - `pnpm typecheck`
  - `pnpm test --filter=[component]`
  - `pnpm lint`
- If a spec file exists for the task, ALWAYS @-mention it in your context
